    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pink-heart-shaped-pasta-with-spicy-cacio-e-pepe-sauce/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pink-heart-shaped-pasta-with-spicy-cacio-e-pepe-sauce/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and your <strong>cracked black pepper</strong></p><p>Cook for 2-3 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pink-heart-shaped-pasta-with-spicy-cacio-e-pepe-sauce/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> fresh pink heart pasta</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the fresh pink heart pasta for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the fresh heart pasta, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pink-heart-shaped-pasta-with-spicy-cacio-e-pepe-sauce/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>clotted cream </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until melted</p><p>Peel your <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong> until you end up with a pile of cheese shavings</p><p>Grate any <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pink-heart-shaped-pasta-with-spicy-cacio-e-pepe-sauce/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong> roughly</p><p>Add your <strong>salad </strong>and the <strong>chopped tomato </strong>to a bowl with your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Gently toss it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>balsamic tomato salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pink-heart-shaped-pasta-with-spicy-cacio-e-pepe-sauce/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the clotted cream has melted, add your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>with a generous splash of the <strong>starchy pasta water </strong>and give everything a good mix up until the cheese has melted</p><p>Once melted, stir through the <strong>cooked pasta </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>cheesy heart shaped pasta with spicy cacio e pepe sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pink-heart-shaped-pasta-with-spicy-cacio-e-pepe-sauce/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>cheesy heart shaped pasta with spicy cacio e pepe sauce </strong>with the <strong>balsamic tomato salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>cheese shavings </strong>and a good grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
